prefix_rule(pattern=["/bin/zsh", "-lc", "gh issue create --repo whaleen/cntx-ui --title \"[DX GAP] agent/query returns no matches for obvious entrypoints and core model files\" --body $'## Context\\nAX audit on `whaleen/tiles` using MCP tools as a brand-new agent.\\n\\n## Repro\\n1. Start MCP server in repo root.\\n2. Call `agent/query` with:\\n   - \"What is the main entry point of this project?\"\\n   - \"Which file is the Rust API entrypoint with fn main?\"\\n   - \"What is the primary data model in this project?\"\\n3. Observe response.\\n\\n## Actual\\n`agent/query` repeatedly returns:\\n- \"No direct semantic matches found. Try refining your query.\"\\n- empty `evidence` and `relatedFiles`\\n\\n## Why this is a DX gap\\nThese are first-hour onboarding questions. The repo has obvious candidates:\\n- `apps/tiles-api/src/main.rs`\\n- `apps/tiles-api/src/models.rs`\\nSo output is misleading and not actionable.\\n\\n## Expected\\nEven with low confidence, return a ranked shortlist of candidate files with reasons + confidence instead of empty results.'"], decision="allow")
prefix_rule(pattern=["/bin/zsh", "-lc", "gh issue create --repo whaleen/cntx-ui --title \"[DX GAP] agent/discover bundle purposes are generic and output is too noisy for first-pass onboarding\" --body $'## Context\\nAX audit on `whaleen/tiles` using `agent/discover` as first touchpoint.\\n\\n## Actual\\n- Discovery includes very long file lists for each bundle (high noise).\\n- Many bundle purposes are generic (`\"General Module\"`).\\n- Semantic grouping sometimes mixes unlike concerns (e.g., docs/config/routes in utility bucket).\\n\\n## Why this is a DX gap\\nFor a new agent, discovery should produce a high-signal map of architecture quickly. The current output is hard to scan and purpose labels are often too vague to guide action.\\n\\n## Expected\\n- Default compact mode with top-level architecture summary + top 3-5 key files per bundle.\\n- Non-generic purpose labels inferred from code intent (e.g., \"Rust API routing\", \"React data hooks\", \"Media processing services\").\\n- Optional `verbose=true` for full file enumerations.'"], decision="allow")
prefix_rule(pattern=["/bin/zsh", "-lc", "gh issue create --repo whaleen/cntx-ui --title \"[DX GAP] agent/investigate returns generic TBD plan instead of file-level integration points\" --body $'## Context\\nAX audit on `whaleen/tiles`, running `agent/investigate` with feature prompt `Feature X`.\\n\\n## Actual\\nResponse contained empty arrays for `existing`, `related`, `integration` and approach:\\n- `\"strategy\": \"TBD\"`\\n- `\"description\": \"Ready to plan\"`\\n\\n## Why this is a DX gap\\nThis output is not actionable and does not help replace manual discovery. The value of investigate mode is concrete insertion points and likely touch files.\\n\\n## Expected\\n- Return specific candidate files/dirs and rationale (e.g., `apps/tiles-api/src/routes/*.rs`, `apps/tiles-studio/src/hooks/*`, etc.).\\n- Include confidence and impact radius.\\n- If confidence is low, still provide top candidates + clarifying assumptions, not empty placeholders.'"], decision="allow")
